## Preface: The Foundation of Position Sizing

### The Secret to Trading Success

- **Position sizing** is the greatest secret to top trading and investing success, yet few people understand it
- Often confused with risk control, money management, diversification, or "how to wisely invest money"
- The key distinction: position sizing refers to the algorithm that tells you **"how much"** to trade with respect to any particular position in the market
- Entry price to become trader/investor is low—all you need is enough money to open an account and understand the risks
- However, most people who open accounts lose money because they don't understand position sizing

### The Central Thesis

> "The purpose of position sizing is to meet your objectives."

- Position sizing is **not** about having one objective (like maximum profits)
- Traders have infinite possible objectives, and thus infinite ways to use position sizing
- Must define objectives **before** developing a trading system
- Although systems have little to do with meeting objectives, position sizing is designed to do exactly that

### The System Quality Number (SQN)

- **Higher System Quality Number**, the easier it is to use position sizing to meet your objectives
- This is a quantifiable relationship: quality directly impacts how useful position sizing becomes
- Even a mediocre system with proper position sizing can meet objectives
- System quality relates to expectancy and other measurable factors

### Why This Book Matters

- One of the most important books for professional investors/traders
- Material provides foundation for everything traders/investors do
- Only personal psychological work is more important than understanding position sizing
- Many psychological biases prevent people from practicing sound position sizing
- Practical considerations include not understanding position sizing or lacking sufficient funds
- To master trading/investing, must thoroughly understand all material in this book

### How to Use This Book

- Four primary sections: (1) golden rules and system evaluation, (2) position sizing basics, (3) using position sizing to meet objectives, (4) miscellaneous topics
- Contains most important technical information traders ever encounter—also the least understood
- Chapter 19 includes mini-test on topics to gauge comprehension
- Must master material to apply it without significant mistakes
- **www.iitm.com** provides glossary and support resources

