### Introduction to Position Sizing Basics

- **3 equity models** and **31 position sizing models** presented in Part II
  → 93 possible model combinations (each equity model × each sizing model)
- Chapters overview:
  - **Ch. 6**: How a low-risk idea is formed; psychological biases against
    proper position sizing
  - **Ch. 7**: CPR for traders — the basic idea behind all position sizing;
    three basic equity models
  - **Ch. 8**: Five core models — fixed units, equal units, percent margin,
    percent volatility, percent risk (**fixed fractional**)
  - **Ch. 9**: Six additional models — group control, portfolio heat,
    long/short positions, asset allocation as position sizing, sizing
    when equity is unknown
  - **Ch. 10**: Impact of various models on equity curve

