### High-End Software (Alternative to Building Your Own)

- Most professional hedge funds/CTAs simply hire programmers (~$250,000+
  minimum) and build proprietary software — **Tom Basso** (Trendstat)
  confirmed: "I doubt [commercial software is used] because they all develop
  their own software"
- For traders with moderate budgets (~$30,000/year programming costs),
  high-end commercial alternatives exist

### Mechanica Pro (Bob Spear)

- Beta-tested for years; actively managing CTA money at time of writing
- Website claim: "Puts you on a level playing field with the biggest CTAs"
- Everything in Mechanica Standard plus:
  1. **Dynamic Risk Management**: resize any position at any time based on
     any portfolio variable; dynamically resize open positions based on
     any combination of portfolio-level conditions — enables full market's
     money and advanced scaling strategies
  2. **Multiple account control**: one installation manages multiple client
