### System 3-1 (High W/L Ratio, Low Win%)

**Trade Distribution:**
- 7 trades at -1R, 1 at -5R, 2 at +10R
- **Expectancy:** 0.80R | **StdDev:** 4.82 | **Win%:** 20.0 | **W/L Ratio:** 6.67 | **# Trades:** 10

**System Summary (100-trade simulation):**
- 25 trades/month | Prob. break-even or higher: **96%**
- Avg drawdown: -27.6R | Avg peak gain: 89.5R | Avg ending gain: 79.1R
- Losing streaks avg: 15 | 95% drawdown duration: 3.5 months

**Position Sizing Optimizer Results:**

| Approach     | Prob. Obj. | Prob. Ruin | Risk% |
|--------------|-----------|-----------|-------|
| Max Return   | 3.4%      | 96.2%     | 14.4% |
| Med Return   | 62.7%     | 24.3%     | 3.2%  |
| Opt. Retire  | 67.5%     | 12.4%     | 2.4%  |
| <1% Ruin     | 56.2%     | 0.8%      | 1.2%  |
| >0% Ruin     | 35.9%     | 0.1%      | 0.8%  |
| Retire-Ruin  | 66.2%     | 5.3%      | 1.8%  |

- Key insight: even a strong system (0.80R expectancy) has 96% ruin at
  max return risk — the optimal retire risk is only **2.4%**

---

### System 3-2 (Moderate, High-Frequency)

**Trade Distribution:**
- 10 trades at -1R, 10 at +1.30R (tight, nearly binary)
- **Expectancy:** 0.15R | **StdDev:** 1.16 | **Win%:** 50.0 | **W/L Ratio:** 1.30 | **# Trades:** 20

**System Summary:**
- 75 trades/month | Prob. break-even: **90.6%**
- Avg drawdown: -8.7R | Avg ending gain: 15.1R | Losing streaks: 6
- 95% drawdown duration: 2.0 months | Trades needed for break-even (95%): 147

**Optimizer Results:**

| Approach     | Prob. Obj. | Prob. Ruin | Risk% |
|--------------|-----------|-----------|-------|
| Max Return   | 11.8%     | 87.3%     | 29.2% |
| Med Return   | 50.1%     | 28.2%     | 9.8%  |
| Opt. Retire  | 53.7%     | 11.4%     | 6.6%  |
| <1% Ruin     | 31.0%     | 0.7%      | 3.6%  |
| Retire-Ruin  | 53.7%     | 11.4%     | 6.6%  |

- Low expectancy but high frequency → higher optimal risk% than System 3-1
- Still: max return carries 87% ruin probability

---

### System 3-3 (Negative Expectancy — The "Loser")

**Trade Distribution:**
- 1 trade at -10R, 9 at +1R
- **Expectancy:** -0.10R | **StdDev:** 3.30 | **Win%:** 90.0 | **W/L Ratio:** 0.10 | **# Trades:** 10

**System Summary:**
- 60 trades/month | Prob. break-even: **45.1%** (less than coin flip)
- Avg drawdown: -42.2R | Avg ending gain: **-10.0R** (negative)
- Losing streaks: 2 (rare but catastrophic) | Trades needed for break-even: **2,968**
- 95% drawdown duration: **49.5 months** (~4 years)

**Optimizer Results:**
- Max Return, Med Return: 0.0% probability of objective — **unoptimizable**
- Opt. Retire: 6.0% risk, 43.0% prob obj, but **avg gain -14.2E+0** (still losing)
- Ruin probability essentially 0 — not because it's safe, but because
  there's no achievable objective; the system destroys capital slowly

> **Key lesson:** High win% with a tiny W/L ratio (0.10) produces
> negative expectancy. 90 winners out of 100 means nothing if each
> rare loser is 10× the winner size. The optimizer cannot rescue a
> negative-expectancy system — it merely controls the rate of loss.

---

### System 3-4 (Trend-Following Style, Very Low Win%)

**Trade Distribution:**
- 55 at -1R, 12 at -2R, 3 at -5R, 5 at +1R, 4 at +5R, 3 at +10R, 3 at +25R
- **Expectancy:** 0.42R | **StdDev:** 5.38 | **Win%:** 17.6 | **W/L Ratio:** 6.45 | **# Trades:** 85

**System Summary:**
- 5 trades/month | Prob. break-even: **77.6%**
- Avg drawdown: -36.6R | Avg peak gain: 61.6R | Avg ending gain: 41.9R
- Losing streaks avg: **17** | Trades needed for break-even (95%): 416
- 95% drawdown duration: **83.2 months** (~7 years) — extreme patience required
- Yearly Gain(R): 25.4 | Avg Yearly Gain / Avg Drawdown: **0.7**

**Optimizer Results:**

| Approach     | Prob. Obj. | Prob. Ruin | Risk% |
|--------------|-----------|-----------|-------|
| Max Return   | 4.7%      | 93.0%     | 9.4%  |
| Med Return   | 17.1%     | 15.2%     | 1.6%  |
| Opt. Retire  | 23.8%     | 42.9%     | 2.8%  |
| <1% Ruin     | 2.7%      | 0.5%      | 0.8%  |
| Retire-Ruin  | 10.1%     | 6.0%      | 1.2%  |

- Low frequency + high variance = brutal drawdown durations
- Even Opt. Retire carries **42.9% ruin** — this system type demands
  very small position sizes or extreme capital reserves

